---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import TopBar from '../components/TopBar.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/CTASection.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Upload Rental Documents — Peter Law · Toronto Real Estate" description="Secure document submission for rental applicants in Toronto. Upload your ID, pay stubs, credit report, and other rental application documents in one place.">

  <TopBar />
  <Header active="rental" />

  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow">Rental · Document upload</div>
      <h1>Upload your rental documents.</h1>
      <p class="article-lead">Send me everything you'd attach to an Ontario rental application in one upload, and I'll take it from there. No back-and-forth email chain.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="major" style="padding-top:24px;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="prose-grid">
        <aside class="prose-side">
          <h4>On this page</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="#what">What to upload</a></li>
            <li><a href="#form">Upload form</a></li>
            <li><a href="#privacy">Privacy &amp; disclaimers</a></li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
        <div class="prose-body">
          <h2 id="what">What to upload</h2>
          <p>The standard Ontario rental application packet a landlord will ask for:</p>
          <ul class="bullets">
            <li><strong>Government-issued photo ID</strong> — driver's license or passport (front + back if applicable)</li>
            <li><strong>Proof of income</strong> — last 2-3 pay stubs OR a recent employment letter on company letterhead stating your role, salary, and start date</li>
            <li><strong>Credit report</strong> — most recent Equifax or TransUnion report (free at <a href="https://www.equifax.ca/personal/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">equifax.ca</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>Bank statement</strong> — most recent month, showing balance &amp; deposits</li>
            <li><strong>Previous landlord reference</strong> — name + phone or email (a short paragraph from them is even better)</li>
            <li><strong>OREA Form 410</strong> (Rental Application) — optional but appreciated, speeds things up. I can send you the form if you don't have it.</li>
            <li><strong>Guarantor / co-signer documents</strong> — if your income alone doesn't meet the standard rental-to-income ratio (typically 30%), include the same packet for whoever's co-signing</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="callout"><strong>Newcomers / international workers:</strong> if you don't have Canadian credit history yet, send what you do have — work permit, employment offer, bank statement, and a reference. Landlords accept alternative packages routinely; I'll position it right.</div>

          <h2 id="form">Upload form</h2>
          <div class="google-form-embed">
            <iframe
              src="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSf-8MgRK8TtsFhIJ4VjdWaFN3u3XjabMOwB9d5cP3LA_d8hDg/viewform?embedded=true"
              width="100%"
              height="1400"
              frameborder="0"
              marginheight="0"
              marginwidth="0"
              title="Rental document upload form"
              loading="lazy">
              Loading…
            </iframe>
          </div>

          <h2 id="privacy">Privacy &amp; disclaimers</h2>
          <ul class="bullets">
            <li><strong>Your documents go to me directly</strong>, encrypted in transit. I review them, package them for the landlord, and don't share with anyone else without your explicit consent.</li>
            <li><strong>Retention.</strong> If we close on a unit, I keep your file on record per RECO record-keeping rules. If we don't close, I delete uploaded documents within 90 days of our last contact.</li>
            <li><strong>This form is not a tenancy agreement.</strong> Submitting documents starts a conversation — it doesn't reserve a unit, guarantee approval, or constitute a legal offer.</li>
            <li><strong>Acceptable file types:</strong> PDF, JPG, PNG, HEIC, WebP. Avoid sending ZIP files (some landlords' email systems block them).</li>
            <li><strong>If a file is too large to upload</strong> (over ~10 MB), email it to <a href="mailto:Admin@RealtorPeterLaw.com">Admin@RealtorPeterLaw.com</a> with your name in the subject line.</li>
            <li><strong>Response time.</strong> I review every submission personally and reply within 24 hours, usually same-day.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="legal-note">This page is for sharing documents related to a rental application. It is not a credit check, background check, or legal document submission. By submitting, you confirm the documents are yours to share and accurate to the best of your knowledge.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection heading="Questions before you upload?" lead="If you're not sure what your packet should include — or you're a newcomer without Canadian credit — book a 15-minute call and I'll talk you through it." ctaTitle="Book a call" />
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
